1
00:00:03,303 --> 00:00:04,872
To all passengers.

2
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:09,209
Thank you for using Haneda Airport.

3
00:00:09,243 --> 00:00:12,012
Kenchan, I've arrived.

4
00:00:12,646 --> 00:00:17,784
This aircraft will arrive at Haneda
Airport in approximately 30 minutes.

5
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:19,019
Ryota Nakazawa

6
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:21,321
Thank you for using...

7
00:00:21,655 --> 00:00:24,524
Which train should I take?

8
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:28,595
There's the Keikyu Line, the Monorail,

9
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:29,696
and buses too!

10
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:33,333
Are you sure
you want to live here in Tokyo?

11
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:35,836
You can't even find the right train.

12
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,838
No worries, I'll ask you.

13
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:43,543
By the way,
do you like flashy or simple?

14
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:44,378
Why do you ask?

15
00:00:44,411 --> 00:00:45,312
Which?

16
00:00:46,580 --> 00:00:49,016
Okay, then simple.

17
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:49,850
Why?

18
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,418
It's a secret.

19
00:00:52,252 --> 00:00:54,922
Today's interview
is with Otowado, right?

20
00:00:55,489 --> 00:00:58,392
You're going to be really busy
once you start.

21
00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:03,463
I'm applying for the Office Equipment
Department. No overtime.

22
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,366
Yeah, sounds perfect for you.

23
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,535
Otowado is a stable company, too.

24
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,673
That's right. Stability is everything.

25
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:16,076
2005

26
00:01:16,209 --> 00:01:17,778
Wow, Kenchan.

27
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:21,782
I'm gonna be a soccer player
when I grow up.

28
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:25,586
But he's all grown up now,
a fine certified public accountant.

29
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:26,853
Hioki Kenya

30
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,322
My name is Hioki.

31
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,058
What's your dream?

32
00:01:32,025 --> 00:01:33,460
Me?

33
00:01:35,228 --> 00:01:39,967
In a mid-sized shopping street
in a mid-sized town in Kumamoto,

34
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:43,470
is a mid-sized bookstore, my home.

35
00:01:45,339 --> 00:01:48,709
My dad "dreamed"
of becoming a writer.

36
00:01:48,742 --> 00:01:50,978
So my mom told us all the time...

37
00:01:51,712 --> 00:01:53,981
Normal is best.

38
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:58,952
Look, you girls must find yourself
a normal boy with a stable job.

39
00:01:58,986 --> 00:02:00,053
And get married.

40
00:02:00,854 --> 00:02:02,055
All. The. Time.

41
00:02:02,889 --> 00:02:04,458
So that became my dream.

42
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:06,760
My dream is to lead a normal life.

43
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,362
What I want to be when I grow up

44
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:14,134
All I wish for is a stable living.

45
00:02:15,702 --> 00:02:18,105
People might laugh.

46
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:20,574
It's 2014, New Year's Day.

47
00:02:20,607 --> 00:02:25,212
Celebrities are off to Hawaii
and Australia for a winter holiday.

48
00:02:25,512 --> 00:02:28,882
Only the lucky few
get to lead a special life.

49
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,884
- Happy New Year!
- You too.

50
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:32,185
Where to?

51
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,321
To Australia for a couple of weeks.

52
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:35,088
Ms. Nami Suzuki

53
00:02:35,088 --> 00:02:36,823
What will you be doing there?

54
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:40,327
Just get away from work for a while
and relax.

55
00:02:41,595 --> 00:02:44,498
As long as my life isn't the worst.

56
00:02:44,531 --> 00:02:45,399
So...

57
00:02:51,471 --> 00:02:54,741
Normal, average, stable.
Nothing beats that.

58
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:57,978
My stability...

59
00:03:12,759 --> 00:03:14,494
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:21,068 --> 00:03:22,669
Tokyo is scary...

61
00:03:28,341 --> 00:03:31,378
Otowado Publishers

62
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:32,712
Here it is.

63
00:03:47,627 --> 00:03:51,431
I'm here for the interview
for the Office Equipment Department.

64
00:03:51,465 --> 00:03:53,066
For the job interview?

65
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,068
I have an appointment for 3 PM.

66
00:03:55,635 --> 00:03:57,304
3 PM...?

67
00:04:07,013 --> 00:04:08,849
Shoot, I'm already nervous.

68
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:32,939
Um...

69
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:40,447
Are you going to sit?

70
00:04:41,648 --> 00:04:42,516
Why?

71
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,284
You're staring at it.

72
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,453
Of course not.

73
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:53,960
Your butt!

74
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:10,377
Saved.

75
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,083
It's...

76
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:19,186
Look.

77
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:21,588
Fresh paint

78
00:05:24,057 --> 00:05:24,824
No way!

79
00:05:27,561 --> 00:05:29,396
Yeah, that's pretty bad...

80
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:30,697
Oh no...

81
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:33,700
I have a job interview!
I can't go like this.

82
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:35,969
You'll get paint on the chairs.

83
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,437
That's so not the point.

84
00:05:39,372 --> 00:05:41,474
Hi Mom? I need help!

85
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:43,343
I got paint on my suit.

86
00:05:43,376 --> 00:05:45,011
But it's actually pretty cool.

87
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:47,013
Chill.

88
00:05:48,315 --> 00:05:50,717
The interview? It's at 3 PM.

89
00:05:51,151 --> 00:05:53,019
Aoyama?

90
00:05:53,053 --> 00:05:54,754
Aoyama Itchome Station is...

91
00:05:54,788 --> 00:05:56,089
The suit shop?

92
00:05:57,057 --> 00:05:58,959
There's no Walmart either.

93
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:01,595
- Only buildings.
- Hey!

94
00:06:01,628 --> 00:06:03,096
What?

95
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,865
I know a place nearby
that sells suits.

96
00:06:07,934 --> 00:06:09,302
The interview is at three, right?

97
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:11,404
Come on.

98
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:13,707
Hurry, we don't have time!

99
00:06:14,641 --> 00:06:16,943
- Huh, wait...
- Hurry!

100
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:24,618
Such a fancy shop...

101
00:06:24,651 --> 00:06:27,988
Let's go for a muted color setup.

102
00:06:28,355 --> 00:06:30,724
The fringes will give
a sophisticated air.

103
00:06:30,757 --> 00:06:32,025
Muted...?

104
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:33,126
I like it.

105
00:06:34,361 --> 00:06:36,329
But my suit jacket is fine.

106
00:06:36,363 --> 00:06:38,498
It's a setup. Try these on.

107
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:40,200
- Huh?
- Here.

108
00:06:42,035 --> 00:06:43,236
What's a setup?

109
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:48,541
Nice, looking good.

110
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,779
I think you could use
a little playfulness.

111
00:06:55,115 --> 00:06:56,049
Here.

112
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:03,256
This will bring you good luck.

113
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,361
You look wonderful.

114
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:13,033
- I have to go.
- Right.

115
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:15,001
- I'll take these.
- Thank you.

116
00:07:15,035 --> 00:07:18,271
No way, hold on!

117
00:07:18,305 --> 00:07:20,640
- I can't let you.
- It's my fault, too.

118
00:07:20,674 --> 00:07:21,941
No, I'll pay.

119
00:07:21,975 --> 00:07:25,011
You've already done so much.

120
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:27,747
Okay.

121
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:30,784
Good luck with your interview.

122
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:32,485
Bye now.

123
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:44,564
Here is your total.

124
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:47,067
Right, thank you.

125
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:54,774
This is quite a blow.

126
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:57,110
Um...

127
00:07:57,544 --> 00:07:59,112
I believe you've made a mistake.

128
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:02,115
22,800 yen right?

129
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,883
Not quite, ma'am.

130
00:08:04,451 --> 00:08:07,320
- 2,280?
- It's 228,000 yen.

131
00:08:13,593 --> 00:08:15,995
228,000 yen...?

132
00:08:16,763 --> 00:08:18,331
Job Interviews

133
00:08:18,465 --> 00:08:19,232
Thank you.

134
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:34,447
Hey Sis, I have a junior high reunion
next week.

135
00:08:34,481 --> 00:08:36,516
- Can I wear this?
- No.

136
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:40,153
Come on,
you didn't get the job anyways.

137
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,021
Don't say that.

138
00:08:42,422 --> 00:08:44,758
I'm just saying the truth.

139
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:48,561
Mom, I want expensive clothes, too.

140
00:08:48,595 --> 00:08:49,929
Something from Tokyo.

141
00:08:49,963 --> 00:08:54,834
They're all the same.
As if we have the money.

142
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:58,238
So, did you call Kenchan?

143
00:08:58,738 --> 00:09:00,373
- Not yet.
- Poor boy.

144
00:09:00,407 --> 00:09:03,243
He must still think
you're going to Tokyo.

145
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:08,114
He's a public accountant now.
How stable!

146
00:09:08,148 --> 00:09:09,783
Watch out for Tokyo girls.

147
00:09:09,816 --> 00:09:11,651
Give me a break.

148
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,922
How do I pay my student loan...

149
00:09:22,128 --> 00:09:23,096
It's Kenchan.

150
00:09:23,430 --> 00:09:25,131
No, it's not.

151
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:28,668
Yes?

152
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:32,238
Am I speaking with Ms. Nami Suzuki?

153
00:09:32,272 --> 00:09:35,408
I'm Handa with Otowado Publishers.

154
00:09:37,177 --> 00:09:40,713
Thank you for applying to
our company the other day.

155
00:09:41,347 --> 00:09:47,320
Sadly, we've already chosen another
for the Office Equipment Department.

156
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:51,124
But we're actually looking for
a Global Fashion Expert Partner.

157
00:09:51,724 --> 00:09:53,827
Groovy fancy expo...?

158
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:55,128
No, all wrong.

159
00:09:55,161 --> 00:09:57,730
It's basically clerical work.

160
00:09:58,231 --> 00:09:59,232
Clerical work?

161
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:03,403
Well not really,
but if you're interested...

162
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:04,537
Yes!

163
00:10:04,904 --> 00:10:07,574
Otowado Publishers
is going to hire me?

164
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:10,810
Yes, I'd love to do it!

165
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,952
Dad, Mom.

166
00:10:21,955 --> 00:10:23,890
I'm leaving.

167
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:29,262
I'm going to live happily in Tokyo!

168
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:53,920
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

169
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:07,433
Excuse me,
where's the Editing Department?

170
00:11:07,467 --> 00:11:10,303
Um, the Worldwide...

171
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:11,304
You mean Miyavi?

172
00:11:13,706 --> 00:11:15,375
The 10th floor.

173
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:17,143
Thank you.

174
00:11:18,578 --> 00:11:19,712
One minute.

175
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:24,017
Is this your first day here?

176
00:11:24,551 --> 00:11:25,351
Yes.

177
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:27,220
Good luck.

178
00:11:28,955 --> 00:11:30,223
Thank you.

179
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,930
Vice President, your car is waiting.

180
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:39,666
Off to battle we go.

181
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:47,307
Good morning.
I'm Suzuki and I'm starting today!

182
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:55,248
Where's the person in charge?

183
00:11:55,281 --> 00:11:58,585
The editor-in-chief isn't here yet.
Unpack your things.

184
00:12:02,455 --> 00:12:05,124
- Excuse me, where's my desk?
- Don't ask me.

185
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:07,193
Hey.

186
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:08,928
- Out of my way.
- Sorry.

187
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:13,066
Why, you must be Nami Suzuki.

188
00:12:13,099 --> 00:12:18,338
- Global Fashion Expertner...
- Global Fashion Expert Partner.

189
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:19,806
Perfect. Go to Aoyama.

190
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:21,975
- The suit shop?
- Of course not.

191
00:12:22,008 --> 00:12:23,776
Mr. Handa!

192
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:27,046
The restaurant Plaisir, in Aoyama.
Look it up.

193
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,349
You'll know what to do. Now go.

194
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:43,396
Welcome.

195
00:12:45,031 --> 00:12:48,167
Hi, I'm here with Otowado Publishers.

196
00:12:48,201 --> 00:12:50,236
Ms. Horai is over there.

197
00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:53,940
Thanks.

198
00:12:58,911 --> 00:13:01,881


199
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:05,518


200
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:12,892
Um, I'm here from Otowado Publishers.

201
00:13:12,925 --> 00:13:13,726
Take the bags.

202
00:13:17,664 --> 00:13:21,134
Huh? Wait, I...

203
00:13:26,739 --> 00:13:27,807
Excuse me!

204
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,376
- And these?
- Take them.

205
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,478
Now go.

206
00:13:39,085 --> 00:13:39,852
What about me?

207
00:13:40,853 --> 00:13:43,890
And what about these?

208
00:13:48,027 --> 00:13:49,896
I'm back.

209
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:51,397
Good work.

210
00:13:53,766 --> 00:13:55,101
Is she a model?

211
00:13:55,635 --> 00:13:59,806
I couldn't believe her.
She was like, "Take the bags."

212
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,843
I guess models are really like that
in real life.

213
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:12,819
Everyone here?

214
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:15,288
Yes, everyone gather around.

215
00:14:15,655 --> 00:14:16,589
Now then.

216
00:14:16,622 --> 00:14:21,894
This is the editor-in-chief
for the new magazine, Miyavi.

217
00:14:21,928 --> 00:14:23,563
Ms. Reiko Horai.

218
00:14:25,064 --> 00:14:26,032
I'm Horai.

219
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:27,633
Editor-in-chief?

220
00:14:27,667 --> 00:14:29,102
It's really her!

221
00:14:29,135 --> 00:14:30,002
Look at her legs.

222
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:33,339
That Fendi purse isn't even out yet!

223
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:34,507
I knew it.

224
00:14:35,007 --> 00:14:39,812
There are many international
fashion magazines all over the world.

225
00:14:39,846 --> 00:14:42,482
For example, Vogue.

226
00:14:42,982 --> 00:14:44,617
Launched in the US,

227
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:49,922
it's now published in England, Italy,
Japan, and 23 other regions.

228
00:14:49,956 --> 00:14:53,926
Miyavi will be a fashion magazine
born in Japan, read around the world.

229
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:57,830
It will break through the icy winter
of the publishing world.

230
00:14:57,864 --> 00:15:03,603
We will create a sensation
in the fashion sphere with Miyavi.

231
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,845
To ensure that this project
is a success,

232
00:15:12,879 --> 00:15:16,616
we've summoned Ms. Horai
straight from Paris.

233
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:21,120
You all here, including me,
are the elites of this company.

234
00:15:21,788 --> 00:15:27,560
Let's take the publishing world
and fashion world by storm!

235
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:29,929
With this, Miyavi!

236
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:34,233
Excuse me.

237
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,370
I've only worked in culture magazines
and...

238
00:15:37,403 --> 00:15:40,940
Find someone to listen to your woes
after work hours.

239
00:15:43,142 --> 00:15:45,845
I'm here to get results.

240
00:15:46,245 --> 00:15:47,980
Miyavi will go on sale in two months

241
00:15:48,014 --> 00:15:51,150
and publish 300,000 copies
in six months.

242
00:15:51,184 --> 00:15:52,385
In two months?

243
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:53,753
300,000...

244
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:54,887
In this digital age?

245
00:15:55,288 --> 00:15:57,857
You're all here to get results.

246
00:15:58,224 --> 00:16:01,127
I do not need incompetent people
who can't.

247
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:05,231
I have a question.

248
00:16:06,098 --> 00:16:09,202
This is my first day here
and I don't understand...

249
00:16:09,769 --> 00:16:12,572
- Is she here on a field trip?
- She'll do odd jobs.

250
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:14,273
Come here.

251
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:15,875
You said I was a Global Fashion...

252
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,310
Yeah, meaning odd jobs.

253
00:16:18,044 --> 00:16:19,478
- Secretary?
- Odd jobs.

254
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,080
Assistant.

255
00:16:21,113 --> 00:16:24,550
You know, like with sumo wrestlers
and celebrities. An attendant.

256
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:25,718
An attendant?

257
00:16:25,751 --> 00:16:28,421
Let's start the editorial meeting.

258
00:16:28,454 --> 00:16:31,457
Wait, I need to ask you something.

259
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,492
I heard magazine editors
work long hours.

260
00:16:33,526 --> 00:16:35,361
What will my hours be?

261
00:16:35,394 --> 00:16:38,297
Don't mind her! Forget about days off.

262
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:39,332
But my schedule.

263
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:41,300
Who cares.

264
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:43,736
Look, you might not understand.

265
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:48,708
Ms. Horai was the editor-in-chief
for Marie Claire in Europe.

266
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:51,477
The first Japanese ever.
She's charismatic.

267
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:55,047
When she smiles
is when money starts rolling.

268
00:16:55,314 --> 00:16:58,050
People call it the devil's grin.

269
00:16:58,384 --> 00:16:59,452
What the heck?

270
00:16:59,485 --> 00:17:01,787
So here's your job.

271
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:06,025
Have coffee ready
when Ms. Horai comes in.

272
00:17:06,058 --> 00:17:10,029
All milk ristretto shot non-syrup
soy latte. Tall.

273
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:13,766
Reserve bullet train
and plane tickets.

274
00:17:14,567 --> 00:17:16,102
Arrange taxi cabs.

275
00:17:16,135 --> 00:17:17,937
Taxi! Here!

276
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:19,605
Taxi!

277
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,708
Carry baggage.

278
00:17:23,442 --> 00:17:25,811
Take memos and communicate it
to the team.

279
00:17:25,845 --> 00:17:30,216
For skirts, I need fringed, peplum,
tiered, balloon, and tulle.

280
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,451
Tulle?

281
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:36,956
And anything else she asks.

282
00:17:39,692 --> 00:17:44,797
Get the pieces from the new collection
and bijoux clutch from Togo Tomari.

283
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:47,099
And the new coat from Fendi,

284
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:49,936
dress from Valentino,
jewelry from Bulgari.

285
00:17:49,969 --> 00:17:54,006
Togo Togori's, new con...?

286
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,008
Togo Tomari's new collection.

287
00:17:56,842 --> 00:17:58,010
Welcome.

288
00:17:58,044 --> 00:18:00,846
I'm looking for Togo and Mari...

289
00:18:01,514 --> 00:18:03,950
Forgive me for asking,
who might you be?

290
00:18:04,684 --> 00:18:07,653
I'm from Otowado Publishers...

291
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,854
What's her name...

292
00:18:08,888 --> 00:18:12,959
I'm sorry, but you need an appointment
in order to...

293
00:18:13,693 --> 00:18:17,663
Reiko Horai! Do you know her?

294
00:18:17,697 --> 00:18:21,400
- Ms. Horai?
- Forgive us!

295
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,970
Right this way.

296
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,138
I'm not your servant.

297
00:18:26,172 --> 00:18:27,273
Understand?

298
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:28,574
I'm back!

299
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:31,310
Jesus.

300
00:18:31,344 --> 00:18:32,278
I like sweets.

301
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:36,382
You may speak
only when I ask you a question.

302
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:38,851
Yes.

303
00:18:59,905 --> 00:19:02,108
I was given these as a gift.

304
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:04,443
But they're really good,
so have some.

305
00:19:05,244 --> 00:19:06,379
Thank you.

306
00:19:08,047 --> 00:19:09,081
How are things?

307
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,217
With your new team.

308
00:19:13,352 --> 00:19:14,854
The team is of no matter.

309
00:19:15,521 --> 00:19:17,123
I will get results.

310
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:23,529
Maybe you should loosen up a bit.

311
00:19:25,898 --> 00:19:26,665
I'm fine.

312
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:29,835
Won't you join me for lunch?

313
00:19:30,403 --> 00:19:31,771
T-today?

314
00:19:31,804 --> 00:19:33,939
Sure. Are you busy?

315
00:19:35,374 --> 00:19:37,276
L-lunch?

316
00:19:38,144 --> 00:19:40,046
You don't have to. Don't worry.

317
00:19:40,646 --> 00:19:41,714
Maybe next time.

318
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:43,215
Um.

319
00:19:45,384 --> 00:19:49,055
I will get you the results
in six months.

320
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:52,391
I'm counting on you.

321
00:20:02,134 --> 00:20:04,036
- It's nice, huh?
- I like it.

322
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,905
Leave these out.

323
00:20:10,676 --> 00:20:11,811
Don't mind me, Handa.

324
00:20:11,844 --> 00:20:14,013
Good work, team.

325
00:20:22,521 --> 00:20:23,556
Not here, huh.

326
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:34,834
Yes, yes. I'm on my way.

327
00:20:34,867 --> 00:20:35,868
Yes, sorry!

328
00:20:37,036 --> 00:20:38,604
That's it, good.

329
00:20:39,505 --> 00:20:40,873
Nice eyes.

330
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:43,609
The other side now.

331
00:20:44,477 --> 00:20:45,511
Look up here.

332
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:47,713
That's it, nice.

333
00:20:51,717 --> 00:20:52,918
Let's take a break.

334
00:21:02,394 --> 00:21:03,395
Jun.

335
00:21:04,597 --> 00:21:06,198
I made this for you.

336
00:21:06,699 --> 00:21:07,466
Here.

337
00:21:08,434 --> 00:21:09,201
Let me take a pic.

338
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:10,803
Mr. Jun!

339
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:16,909
Ugh no, not me.

340
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:19,078
You've got a visitor.

341
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,085
It's been a while, Junnosuke.

342
00:21:26,485 --> 00:21:27,753
What is it?

343
00:21:28,654 --> 00:21:30,789
I know what you're going to say.

344
00:21:30,823 --> 00:21:32,825
I don't have time,
so I'll make it quick.

345
00:21:33,192 --> 00:21:35,828
I have to run back to Kanazawa.

346
00:21:36,529 --> 00:21:39,031
I think you'll like this one.

347
00:21:39,398 --> 00:21:43,002
The daughter of the president
of one of our clients.

348
00:21:47,039 --> 00:21:49,575
You can at least look at her picture.

349
00:21:49,608 --> 00:21:51,177
Sorry, but no thanks.

350
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:54,947
An omelet over rice
and an iced coffee please.

351
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:57,249
Do this for your poor mother.

352
00:21:57,283 --> 00:22:01,220
- Don't worry, I'll run the company.
- Whenever that's going to be.

353
00:22:01,554 --> 00:22:05,124
You can't play around
and be a photographer forever.

354
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:07,960
So hurry up and get married.

355
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,962
And come back home.

356
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:11,864
I know.

357
00:22:12,231 --> 00:22:13,432
But not marriage.

358
00:22:13,465 --> 00:22:15,968
What, do you have a girlfriend?

359
00:22:17,436 --> 00:22:21,173
If you do, then introduce me to her.

360
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:24,210
I gotta go.

361
00:22:26,979 --> 00:22:29,648
You haven't eaten your omelet yet.

362
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:39,625
Jun! Your lunch.

363
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:43,829
Hey, can I ask you a favor?

364
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:46,932
Sure, I'll do anything for you.

365
00:22:50,336 --> 00:22:51,203
Never mind.

366
00:22:51,904 --> 00:22:55,541
Victoria Kroos. Charlotte Hooper.
Olivia Vinx.

367
00:22:55,574 --> 00:22:57,977
All super models
from Paris Fashion Week.

368
00:22:58,010 --> 00:23:00,212
They have the looks
and the name value.

369
00:23:01,113 --> 00:23:03,015
I like it. Right, Ms. Horai?

370
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:10,222
No way. It's the cover
for the first issue, understand?

371
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:15,628
Why don't we debut a new model?

372
00:23:16,161 --> 00:23:17,730
Good idea.

373
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:21,667
Debuting a fresh new gem
for our very first cover.

374
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,302
How about it?

375
00:23:25,871 --> 00:23:27,273
No way, nope.

376
00:23:27,306 --> 00:23:31,510
There's no such person.
If there were, show me, huh?

377
00:23:31,844 --> 00:23:34,613
- You must be an idiot.
- Sorry.

378
00:23:37,483 --> 00:23:40,219
Miyavi is about
bringing Japan to the world.

379
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:44,223
So we're going to use
a world-class Japanese model.

380
00:23:46,492 --> 00:23:47,693
I've arranged it.

381
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:50,929
I managed to book her
three days from today.

382
00:23:51,497 --> 00:23:52,932
Such short notice!

383
00:23:53,365 --> 00:23:54,633
Get a studio and staffing!

384
00:23:57,703 --> 00:24:00,939
But what about the design
for the cover?

385
00:24:02,341 --> 00:24:03,575
I'll have it by then.

386
00:24:03,609 --> 00:24:05,144
I'll leave the rest to you.

387
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:06,879
I'm back.

388
00:24:08,681 --> 00:24:10,883
Oh Jesus.

389
00:24:11,317 --> 00:24:14,053
Taxi, outside in 30 minutes.

390
00:24:14,086 --> 00:24:14,853
A taxi?

391
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:24,496
Ouch...

392
00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:33,939
That dress.

393
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:36,909
I'm going to lunch.
Have a taxi ready when I'm done.

394
00:24:37,876 --> 00:24:41,947
Receive and organize
everything that arrives at my office.

395
00:24:43,182 --> 00:24:45,718
Isn't that the dress
I just went and got?

396
00:24:46,251 --> 00:24:50,856
I thought it was for the magazine.

397
00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:54,660
Did I ask you a question?

398
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:59,365
You may speak
only when I ask you a question.

399
00:24:59,398 --> 00:25:00,466
But...

400
00:25:01,734 --> 00:25:03,602
Understand?

401
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:11,343
Yes.

402
00:25:19,651 --> 00:25:22,688
Why am I so darn busy from day one?

403
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:28,227
I'm finally in Tokyo,
but I can't see Kenchan.

404
00:25:30,696 --> 00:25:35,367
I just want a normal life.
Let me rest like a normal human.

405
00:25:39,405 --> 00:25:40,339
Good morning.

406
00:25:46,111 --> 00:25:46,879
Where's Ms. Horai?

407
00:25:47,546 --> 00:25:49,815
- The studio, maybe.
- Thank you.

408
00:25:52,718 --> 00:25:56,822
Office Equipment Department

409
00:25:59,825 --> 00:26:01,126
Lucky them.

410
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:08,033
Here's your coffee!

411
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,669
Can I have a little more wind?

412
00:26:11,937 --> 00:26:12,771
Where's Ms. Horai?

413
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:14,606
She was just here.

414
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,945
Yeah, that's good.

415
00:26:20,612 --> 00:26:22,915
Hey, if you're doing nothing, help me.

416
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:25,484
Get me that blouson.

417
00:26:26,552 --> 00:26:27,986
Blouson?

418
00:26:35,194 --> 00:26:36,261
Is this what you mean?

419
00:26:37,062 --> 00:26:38,363
Shoes!

420
00:26:38,397 --> 00:26:39,798
Oh no, sorry!

421
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:44,603
Here's the blouson.

422
00:26:44,703 --> 00:26:46,104
Wrong.

423
00:26:47,873 --> 00:26:48,907
This is a blouson.

424
00:26:53,245 --> 00:26:54,713
Here you go.

425
00:26:58,650 --> 00:26:59,651
Mr. Nakazawa.

426
00:27:01,086 --> 00:27:03,489
I'm sorry about earlier.

427
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:16,835
The least you can do
is understand the language.

428
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:19,137
Don't get in my way.

429
00:27:20,205 --> 00:27:21,206
I'm sorry.

430
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:25,644
You really studied hard, huh.

431
00:27:26,245 --> 00:27:27,012
Making fun of me?

432
00:27:27,045 --> 00:27:28,447
Not at all!

433
00:27:28,714 --> 00:27:30,682
I'm just really impressed.

434
00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:33,151
If I make my name here,

435
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:36,221
I could become editor-in-chief
of a culture magazine.

436
00:27:37,556 --> 00:27:39,525
Is that your dream?

437
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:41,760
Not really.

438
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:43,629
But...

439
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:48,734
Everyone that works here
feels pretty much the same way.

440
00:27:49,902 --> 00:27:51,136
Except for you.

441
00:27:58,043 --> 00:28:01,213
I told you to have my stuff ready
outside.

442
00:28:01,246 --> 00:28:03,115
When are you getting here?

443
00:28:03,148 --> 00:28:04,016
Sorry, I'm coming!

444
00:28:04,049 --> 00:28:06,785
Oh, and bring something
to sketch with.

445
00:28:07,419 --> 00:28:09,187
Sketch? Okay.

446
00:28:12,090 --> 00:28:15,260
Is "sketch" a fashion term?

447
00:28:30,676 --> 00:28:32,678
- Here it is!
- Open it.

448
00:28:36,181 --> 00:28:38,917
- Get in.
- I can?

449
00:28:38,951 --> 00:28:39,985
Now.

450
00:28:40,652 --> 00:28:42,588
Yes, thank you.

451
00:28:58,337 --> 00:28:59,471
Stop here.

452
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:03,675
Thank you.

453
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,980
Take this back
and you can leave for today.

454
00:29:09,381 --> 00:29:10,415
But it's not even three.

455
00:29:10,449 --> 00:29:14,720
Go to Azabu and buy these sweets,
and that'll be it.

456
00:29:18,890 --> 00:29:20,058
Thank you!

457
00:29:23,962 --> 00:29:24,997
Seriously?

458
00:29:25,697 --> 00:29:27,733
I can finally go see Kenchan.

459
00:29:47,352 --> 00:29:51,089
The queue for our sweets
is currently two hours long.

460
00:29:59,731 --> 00:30:00,632
This is great.

461
00:30:00,632 --> 00:30:01,733
Cancer Insurance

462
00:30:02,534 --> 00:30:04,169
I've prepared two designs.

463
00:30:05,070 --> 00:30:06,905
They're both amazing.

464
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:10,075
We're offering a new plan soon.

465
00:30:10,509 --> 00:30:13,445
We'd like you to make pamphlets
for those, too.

466
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:14,880
Sure, thank you.

467
00:30:16,148 --> 00:30:16,915
So.

468
00:30:18,016 --> 00:30:20,318
I pray your father is well?

469
00:30:21,086 --> 00:30:22,187
My father?

470
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:27,025
Yes, I had the honor of meeting him
at one of his parties.

471
00:30:27,726 --> 00:30:30,228
Please, give him my warmest regards.

472
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:36,501
This is nice.

473
00:30:38,737 --> 00:30:41,006
They want you to do the next one too!

474
00:30:42,074 --> 00:30:43,175
Aren't you happy?

475
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:45,844
Yeah. Of course I am.

476
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:56,088
I'll go see you this weekend.
I promise.

477
00:30:56,088 --> 00:30:56,888
This weekend?

478
00:30:56,922 --> 00:30:58,657
It's your birthday.

479
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,058
Well, actually.

480
00:31:00,092 --> 00:31:03,995
My friends are having a party for me
this weekend.

481
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:10,102
Hey, do you want to come too?

482
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:11,403
I can?

483
00:31:12,003 --> 00:31:15,340
It's the best way
to introduce everyone.

484
00:31:16,208 --> 00:31:17,309
Introduce?

485
00:31:17,609 --> 00:31:20,946
You know. Since things are things.

486
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:24,082
I'm so happy.

487
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:28,386
Yeah, I'll definitely go.
I can't wait.

488
00:31:33,191 --> 00:31:34,793
He's going to introduce me.

489
00:31:44,102 --> 00:31:45,804
What are you doing?

490
00:31:50,809 --> 00:31:53,211
This isn't what I signed up for.

491
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:55,914
Then what was that little dance about?

492
00:31:57,415 --> 00:31:58,683
Oh, that's different.

493
00:31:59,351 --> 00:32:03,722
This weekend, Kenchan...

494
00:32:03,755 --> 00:32:06,892
He's a childhood friend.
He's having a birthday party.

495
00:32:07,726 --> 00:32:11,129
I'm going to marry him.

496
00:32:11,163 --> 00:32:16,368
And live a normal, stable life.

497
00:32:18,703 --> 00:32:20,472
I won't have to work, will I?

498
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:24,075
Who knows? I'm going to work though.

499
00:32:24,576 --> 00:32:25,944
On a weekend?

500
00:32:26,645 --> 00:32:28,346
I'm just an assistant now.

501
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:32,818
An assistant editor.

502
00:32:33,418 --> 00:32:37,088
But it's always been a dream of mine
to become an editor.

503
00:32:38,390 --> 00:32:41,059
This is a once in a lifetime chance.

504
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:43,929
So I want to learn what I can.

505
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:48,433
I'm going to keep up with her
no matter what.

506
00:32:49,201 --> 00:32:50,569
Dang, you go girl.

507
00:32:51,336 --> 00:32:53,238
It's not just me.

508
00:32:53,271 --> 00:32:57,442
Ms. Kazumi is taking
even more English lessons now.

509
00:32:57,876 --> 00:33:02,180
Mr. Nakazawa used to work in
a cultural magazine.

510
00:33:02,214 --> 00:33:04,783
So he's really studying fashion now.

511
00:33:05,417 --> 00:33:06,318
Oh yeah.

512
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:08,687
This.

513
00:33:09,421 --> 00:33:10,655
He gave me this.

514
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:17,195
It's not for me though.

515
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:19,364
I can't try that hard.

516
00:33:20,999 --> 00:33:25,070
Hey, how was that sketch
Ms. Horai said to give you?

517
00:33:25,103 --> 00:33:27,505
It was mostly scribbles,
but was it okay?

518
00:33:27,906 --> 00:33:29,474
Yeah, I got it.

519
00:33:30,375 --> 00:33:35,447
We drove all over the city
just to draw that one sketch.

520
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,549
I can't handle it anymore.

521
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:41,653
Hey.

522
00:33:42,587 --> 00:33:44,489
If you're just here
until you get married,

523
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,725
why don't you find an easier job?

524
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,362
You know.

525
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:54,532
Only people with real dreams
can do this job.

526
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:25,230
Dreams, huh?

527
00:34:29,434 --> 00:34:32,837
Here is the cake you reserved.

528
00:34:33,171 --> 00:34:34,839
Happy Birthday Kenchan

529
00:34:50,522 --> 00:34:51,289
Welcome.

530
00:34:53,792 --> 00:34:55,727
I might have it at home.

531
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:58,029
What a waste, man!

532
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:01,533
Kenchan.

533
00:35:04,803 --> 00:35:07,172
- You're here.
- Dang, she's cute.

534
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:11,209
Let me introduce you to my fiancée.

535
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:15,347
Sarina.

536
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:22,087
She's the daughter of the owner
of my accounting firm.

537
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:25,190
And this is Nami,
an old friend from back home.

538
00:35:26,291 --> 00:35:28,627
Nice to meet you.
Thank you for coming today.

539
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:31,629
Come on, let's drink.

540
00:35:31,663 --> 00:35:35,467
By the way,
do you like flashy or simple?

541
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:37,869
Fiancée...

542
00:35:37,902 --> 00:35:39,504
Happy Engagement!

543
00:35:40,739 --> 00:35:42,440
I didn't know.

544
00:35:42,474 --> 00:35:44,809
I didn't have the chance
to introduce you.

545
00:35:45,844 --> 00:35:47,278
I'm glad you came.

546
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:51,883
Her family owns a bookstore,
and I read books there every day.

547
00:35:52,784 --> 00:35:55,954
So she's like a little sister to me.

548
00:35:55,987 --> 00:35:59,224
She'd been contacting me recently
on coming to Tokyo.

549
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:05,230
I have to go back to the office.
Some odd stuff to do.

550
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:07,599
- You just got here.
- Sorry.

551
00:36:08,199 --> 00:36:10,769
Thanks for inviting me today.

552
00:36:36,861 --> 00:36:39,431
Nihonbashi Tower, now
Reiko Horai

553
00:36:41,566 --> 00:36:42,333
Sorry.

554
00:36:42,801 --> 00:36:43,601
Not at all.

555
00:36:44,436 --> 00:36:46,771
But that does sound interesting.

556
00:37:07,826 --> 00:37:08,593
Where's the taxi?

557
00:37:09,961 --> 00:37:11,429
We need to talk.

558
00:37:12,163 --> 00:37:16,134
- You...
- Don't worry. I can find one myself.

559
00:37:16,468 --> 00:37:17,368
Later.

560
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:20,638
I'm sorry.

561
00:37:24,042 --> 00:37:24,843
Um.

562
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:28,913
This isn't work.

563
00:37:29,848 --> 00:37:31,683
I'll do odd jobs, I'm a newbie.

564
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:35,386
But only if they're
to make a magazine.

565
00:37:35,687 --> 00:37:40,458
But carrying your things and getting
clothes for you to go on dates.

566
00:37:40,492 --> 00:37:42,660
Flagging taxis for your boyfriend.

567
00:37:44,062 --> 00:37:45,797
I'm not your servant.

568
00:37:50,201 --> 00:37:51,269
So?

569
00:37:51,669 --> 00:37:52,670
I...

570
00:37:53,738 --> 00:37:56,141
I just want a normal average job.

571
00:37:58,977 --> 00:37:59,978
Average?

572
00:38:01,179 --> 00:38:02,413
What's so funny?

573
00:38:04,182 --> 00:38:04,983
Look.

574
00:38:05,583 --> 00:38:11,289
Only those who are above average
are allowed to wish for average.

575
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:15,393
You don't realize how hard
average is to obtain.

576
00:38:16,361 --> 00:38:20,565
Can you make an average magazine
sold in average bookstores?

577
00:38:21,699 --> 00:38:26,171
- But...
- You can't even manage odd jobs.

578
00:38:26,604 --> 00:38:28,773
Average?
Isn't that a bit presumptuous?

579
00:38:30,775 --> 00:38:35,146
As long as you make light of odd jobs,
this job is too much for you.

580
00:38:38,383 --> 00:38:39,250
I understand.

581
00:38:40,018 --> 00:38:41,019
I quit.

582
00:38:42,353 --> 00:38:46,057
No conviction, no drive.

583
00:38:47,926 --> 00:38:49,661
Not even average perseverance.

584
00:40:27,792 --> 00:40:32,730
Happy birthday to you.

585
00:40:33,464 --> 00:40:38,336
Happy birthday to you.

586
00:40:39,737 --> 00:40:41,406
Fresh paint!

587
00:40:43,708 --> 00:40:47,178
I knew it. Those clothes.
Seen them before.

588
00:40:50,848 --> 00:40:52,417
Who's Kenchan?

589
00:40:53,318 --> 00:40:54,953
Why are you eating it alone?

590
00:40:55,620 --> 00:40:56,621
It's complicated.

591
00:40:57,055 --> 00:40:59,657
- You're going to eat it all?
- Of course not.

592
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:04,062
Anyways, I wanted to thank you.

593
00:41:05,096 --> 00:41:08,066
Thanks to you, I made it in time
for the interview.

594
00:41:08,266 --> 00:41:09,500
And I got the job.

595
00:41:10,668 --> 00:41:13,705
The clothes were pretty expensive,
but...

596
00:41:15,340 --> 00:41:16,808
Thank you.

597
00:41:16,841 --> 00:41:18,076
Great for you!

598
00:41:19,911 --> 00:41:22,513
But it wasn't the department I wanted.

599
00:41:22,580 --> 00:41:27,385
And my boss is a bit,
you know, difficult.

600
00:41:28,353 --> 00:41:29,787
So I'm going to quit.

601
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:32,056
That's awful.

602
00:41:32,090 --> 00:41:34,058
Yeah, it really is.

603
00:41:34,092 --> 00:41:36,794
I feel like I'm kind of to blame.

604
00:41:36,828 --> 00:41:38,730
No, I'm really grateful...

605
00:41:39,797 --> 00:41:40,565
Why?

606
00:41:41,699 --> 00:41:43,267
I like sweets.

607
00:41:43,568 --> 00:41:44,635
Can I eat it?

608
00:41:46,537 --> 00:41:48,072
Sure.

609
00:41:53,277 --> 00:41:55,279
That was yummy.

610
00:41:56,214 --> 00:41:58,216
I'll be going now.

611
00:41:59,617 --> 00:42:00,385
Bye.

612
00:42:01,786 --> 00:42:03,621
- Hey.
- Yes?

613
00:42:04,322 --> 00:42:06,491
Want to go eat something savory now?

614
00:42:56,674 --> 00:42:58,409
The wind feels great.

615
00:42:59,110 --> 00:43:00,178
What, my name?

616
00:43:01,679 --> 00:43:03,781
The wind feels great!

617
00:43:03,815 --> 00:43:05,450
I'm Junnosuke.

618
00:43:06,451 --> 00:43:07,618
Oh, okay.

619
00:43:23,234 --> 00:43:24,602
We came pretty far.

620
00:43:25,303 --> 00:43:26,137
It's...

621
00:43:28,239 --> 00:43:29,140
The ocean.

622
00:43:33,511 --> 00:43:34,979
Weren't we going to eat?

623
00:43:35,012 --> 00:43:38,282
I got lost on the way.

624
00:43:38,850 --> 00:43:40,384
Didn't think I'd come this far.

625
00:43:43,187 --> 00:43:44,755
We're in Chiba.

626
00:43:45,089 --> 00:43:48,659
It's the ocean! Yeah!

627
00:43:56,901 --> 00:43:58,469
What a free soul.

628
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:06,577
The ocean is the best
when you're feeling the worst.

629
00:44:06,944 --> 00:44:08,379
Why's that?

630
00:44:09,046 --> 00:44:10,414
I dunno.

631
00:44:10,882 --> 00:44:13,651
Like how food tastes better
when you're hungry.

632
00:44:18,289 --> 00:44:19,056
Here.

633
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:21,826
Sweet bean soup?

634
00:44:22,393 --> 00:44:23,995
I like sweets.

635
00:44:34,872 --> 00:44:36,240
It's real sweet.

636
00:44:44,949 --> 00:44:46,851
Feeling better?

637
00:45:00,197 --> 00:45:01,265
That cake.

638
00:45:03,568 --> 00:45:05,403
For "Kenchan."

639
00:45:07,271 --> 00:45:10,141
He's a childhood friend,
three years older than me.

640
00:45:11,876 --> 00:45:14,979
He came to Tokyo last year
for his job.

641
00:45:15,379 --> 00:45:18,216
So I thought I'd come to Tokyo too.

642
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:20,017
Your boyfriend?

643
00:45:20,818 --> 00:45:21,986
No, it's one-sided.

644
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,056
Ever since I was a little girl.

645
00:45:28,025 --> 00:45:29,627
But he's engaged now.

646
00:45:31,929 --> 00:45:34,332
Didn't even get a chance
to be turned down.

647
00:45:37,969 --> 00:45:39,837
Jeez, what am I doing?

648
00:45:41,706 --> 00:45:43,641
Coming all the way out to Tokyo.

649
00:45:44,475 --> 00:45:47,678
Without a dream or anything
like everyone else.

650
00:45:50,014 --> 00:45:54,919
I feel like everyone's moving on
except for me.

651
00:45:58,956 --> 00:46:02,226
Are dreams really that important?

652
00:46:04,295 --> 00:46:06,731
Not that I'm against dreaming.

653
00:46:07,598 --> 00:46:09,300
But you don't need one, do you?

654
00:46:10,768 --> 00:46:12,403
Really?

655
00:46:12,737 --> 00:46:18,109
People can be held back
and bound down by their dreams.

656
00:46:18,809 --> 00:46:20,978
What's the use
if dreams keep you from smiling?

657
00:46:32,390 --> 00:46:34,992
Haruka Izumi

658
00:46:35,726 --> 00:46:36,761
Sorry.

659
00:46:39,764 --> 00:46:40,364
Yes?

660
00:46:40,731 --> 00:46:43,067
The sketch you handed me.

661
00:46:43,934 --> 00:46:46,871
Ms. Horai drew it, right?

662
00:46:46,904 --> 00:46:50,041
The one with lots of flowers?
Yes, she did.

663
00:46:53,944 --> 00:46:54,845
What's wrong?

664
00:46:56,414 --> 00:46:59,183
Nothing, it's my fault anyways.

665
00:46:59,750 --> 00:47:01,585
- Thanks.
- Wait!

666
00:47:01,619 --> 00:47:04,889
What happened?
Did I do something wrong again?

667
00:47:05,756 --> 00:47:07,358
No, I did.

668
00:47:07,992 --> 00:47:11,228
Ms. Horai told me
to prepare some roses.

669
00:47:11,929 --> 00:47:16,333
I thought it was for a gift
for the model or something.

670
00:47:17,501 --> 00:47:18,636
But the roses...

671
00:47:19,770 --> 00:47:22,139
It was for the cover shot.

672
00:47:23,574 --> 00:47:24,575
The shoot...

673
00:47:24,608 --> 00:47:27,578
It's tomorrow morning,
so it's too late to order some.

674
00:47:28,446 --> 00:47:29,747
I'm going to be fired.

675
00:47:30,681 --> 00:47:33,384
I'm going to keep up with her
no matter what.

676
00:47:35,619 --> 00:47:36,921
I'll go buy roses!

677
00:47:36,954 --> 00:47:39,357
No, it's too late now.

678
00:47:39,390 --> 00:47:40,524
Wait for me!

679
00:47:42,226 --> 00:47:44,562
Come on, hurry!

680
00:47:44,595 --> 00:47:47,598
Wait, huh?

681
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:50,000
I thought you were quitting.

682
00:47:50,868 --> 00:47:52,436
I can't let her quit.

683
00:47:55,372 --> 00:47:57,141
Then hold on tight.

684
00:48:26,570 --> 00:48:29,073
Hi, can I have all your roses?

685
00:48:29,940 --> 00:48:32,877
Roses? I'm all out dear.

686
00:48:35,546 --> 00:48:38,115
Mr. Handa is looking for some too?

687
00:48:39,116 --> 00:48:42,253
Yes, so are we. I mean, not we. Me.

688
00:48:42,286 --> 00:48:44,622
This is all they had.

689
00:48:50,861 --> 00:48:52,163
I'll be going now.

690
00:48:52,596 --> 00:48:54,765
Thank you so much.

691
00:49:06,477 --> 00:49:09,079
This is it, huh?

692
00:49:09,113 --> 00:49:11,182
They're in different colors, too.

693
00:49:11,448 --> 00:49:13,818
It's too cold for roses
this time of year.

694
00:49:17,455 --> 00:49:18,255
You all did great.

695
00:49:20,958 --> 00:49:23,794
Why the hell did this happen?

696
00:49:31,702 --> 00:49:33,771
- Um...
- I'm sorry, it's my fault.

697
00:49:34,872 --> 00:49:36,473
I forgot about it.

698
00:49:36,507 --> 00:49:38,809
- You again?
- I'm sorry!

699
00:49:43,581 --> 00:49:46,417
Mr. Handa, about the roses.

700
00:49:46,684 --> 00:49:49,053
- I know where...
- Enough.

701
00:49:49,086 --> 00:49:51,021
I just saw a rose garden.

702
00:49:51,655 --> 00:49:52,890
A rose garden?

703
00:49:52,923 --> 00:49:54,024
I saw a sign
with lots of pretty roses.

704
00:49:54,024 --> 00:49:56,227
Futtsu Rose Garden

705
00:49:59,196 --> 00:50:02,533
We'd have to pick them.
When? How do you get permission?

706
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:06,704
The staff has to arrange them
and be ready to shoot before noon.

707
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:11,375
We can't bring the roses.

708
00:50:12,009 --> 00:50:13,577
But we can take the model.

709
00:50:14,979 --> 00:50:18,616
Remember, the sketch Ms. Horai drew?

710
00:50:18,649 --> 00:50:22,086
See? The model is standing
in front of a wall of roses.

711
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:26,991
On location, huh.

712
00:50:29,159 --> 00:50:30,628
Are you sure it'll work?

713
00:50:32,396 --> 00:50:34,999
I don't know anything
about photography, so...

714
00:50:39,036 --> 00:50:41,872
It's worth a shot.
I'll call Ms. Horai.

715
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:43,941
Where's it at?

716
00:50:46,677 --> 00:50:47,811
Please!

717
00:50:49,446 --> 00:50:51,148
We need to shoot today.

718
00:50:52,783 --> 00:50:53,717
I refuse.

719
00:50:56,987 --> 00:50:58,088
Please.

720
00:50:58,389 --> 00:50:59,990
Mr. Nakazawa.

721
00:51:00,024 --> 00:51:02,660
It's for the cover shot
of our first issue.

722
00:51:02,693 --> 00:51:04,795
Please, we need your help.

723
00:51:05,262 --> 00:51:06,830
- Please.
- Please.

724
00:51:08,766 --> 00:51:10,801
We've had a TV crew here before.

725
00:51:11,702 --> 00:51:15,139
When they were done,
they'd trampled all over the garden.

726
00:51:16,173 --> 00:51:18,542
Ever since,
I've declined all such offers.

727
00:51:19,043 --> 00:51:20,744
We'd never do that.

728
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:23,480
We'll be careful
not to damage the roses.

729
00:51:24,214 --> 00:51:25,316
Please leave.

730
00:51:26,250 --> 00:51:27,284
Wait.

731
00:51:29,787 --> 00:51:30,788
No way...

732
00:51:31,221 --> 00:51:32,556
Who are you?

733
00:51:35,993 --> 00:51:38,696
Your roses are beautiful.

734
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:46,971
It must've been so difficult
growing them in the cold.

735
00:51:48,405 --> 00:51:51,308
You must know of a rose
named Marie Antoinette.

736
00:51:52,509 --> 00:51:56,380
The queen that the rose
was named after

737
00:51:57,047 --> 00:51:59,883
was passionate about
her Versailles garden.

738
00:52:01,585 --> 00:52:07,057
Her white hands were often soiled
and scratched by the roses.

739
00:52:07,758 --> 00:52:08,826
She cared for them
as if they were her children.

740
00:52:12,233 --> 00:52:15,970
Many think of her
as proud and extravagant.

741
00:52:16,503 --> 00:52:18,172
But in truth,

742
00:52:18,205 --> 00:52:22,643
she was a woman who loved flowers
and the beauty of nature.

743
00:52:24,378 --> 00:52:25,145
Yes.

744
00:52:26,747 --> 00:52:28,082
Just like you.

745
00:52:29,116 --> 00:52:32,253
Fashion is about creating
an ephemeral dream.

746
00:52:33,454 --> 00:52:36,123
Your roses have that power.

747
00:52:37,524 --> 00:52:42,129
Let your roses
create a dream-like realm

748
00:52:42,162 --> 00:52:44,465
for women all around the world.

749
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:49,970
We need your help.

750
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:54,675
I beg you.

751
00:53:01,115 --> 00:53:02,082
Get ready to shoot.

752
00:53:03,017 --> 00:53:04,485
- The permission?
- Granted.

753
00:53:04,518 --> 00:53:07,154
- Ms. Horai got down on her knees.
- What?

754
00:53:07,187 --> 00:53:09,323
Ms. Horai, on her knees?

755
00:53:09,356 --> 00:53:11,558
You got permission?

756
00:53:12,526 --> 00:53:14,762
- A bit lower.
- The model is ready.

757
00:53:19,433 --> 00:53:21,735
Reiko, long time no see.

758
00:53:22,469 --> 00:53:23,604
Doing good?

759
00:53:24,138 --> 00:53:26,507
Thanks for coming, Ai.

760
00:53:27,574 --> 00:53:30,144
Anything for you, Reiko.

761
00:53:41,555 --> 00:53:43,023
How is it, Ms. Horai?

762
00:53:43,057 --> 00:53:46,026
Zoom out a bit.
Show the obi belt more.

763
00:53:51,231 --> 00:53:54,001
Thank you, Ms. Suzuki.

764
00:53:55,202 --> 00:53:56,904
I don't think I'll be fired.

765
00:53:58,706 --> 00:54:00,207
Good.

766
00:54:02,443 --> 00:54:05,546
And sorry for saying
such strong words.

767
00:54:06,947 --> 00:54:07,781
Not at all.

768
00:54:10,918 --> 00:54:12,119
That guy.

769
00:54:15,255 --> 00:54:16,357
Togo Tomari?

770
00:54:17,658 --> 00:54:19,593
I've heard that name before.

771
00:54:20,894 --> 00:54:22,062
Ms. Horai's boyfriend?

772
00:54:22,663 --> 00:54:26,800
Of course not.
He's a world famous dyeing artist.

773
00:54:27,201 --> 00:54:29,203
He's known for his flower patterns.

774
00:54:31,238 --> 00:54:34,007
So that's why she needed roses.

775
00:54:34,041 --> 00:54:37,511
She wanted to use Togo Tomari's work
for the cover shot.

776
00:54:40,447 --> 00:54:43,150
He's famous for hating the media.

777
00:54:43,183 --> 00:54:46,153
How did she manage to get to him?

778
00:54:49,056 --> 00:54:51,425
Isn't that the dress
I just went and got?

779
00:54:51,458 --> 00:54:54,094
Getting clothes for you
to go on dates.

780
00:54:54,128 --> 00:54:55,596
This isn't work.

781
00:55:00,134 --> 00:55:02,603
It was for work.

782
00:55:03,203 --> 00:55:05,072
I chose the blue for this.

783
00:55:23,891 --> 00:55:26,193
Please don't honk again.

784
00:55:26,560 --> 00:55:28,762
What if somebody sees us?

785
00:55:29,430 --> 00:55:34,268
What, the vice president meeting
with the rival editor-in-chief?

786
00:55:37,504 --> 00:55:39,740
Just kidding. I won't anymore.

787
00:55:41,074 --> 00:55:44,211
So, how's Reiko? Like always?

788
00:55:46,046 --> 00:55:47,314
You'll see.

789
00:55:48,382 --> 00:55:50,350
You'll see in time.

790
00:56:00,260 --> 00:56:02,296
Ms. Suzuki, look.

791
00:56:03,530 --> 00:56:05,499
Is that the cover shot?

792
00:56:09,803 --> 00:56:12,206
She really does get results.

793
00:56:12,239 --> 00:56:14,441
What, were you doubting her?

794
00:56:14,475 --> 00:56:15,542
Not at all.

795
00:56:16,710 --> 00:56:17,478
How is it?

796
00:56:22,182 --> 00:56:24,985
We need your help.

797
00:56:26,153 --> 00:56:27,087
Please.

798
00:56:35,128 --> 00:56:38,899
So this is going to be on a magazine
and be sold at bookstores.

799
00:56:39,933 --> 00:56:41,134
I can't wait to see it.

800
00:56:44,137 --> 00:56:44,938
I know.

801
00:56:56,617 --> 00:56:57,718
Newbie girl.

802
00:56:58,719 --> 00:57:01,188
- Ms. Suzuki.
- Yes.

803
00:57:01,221 --> 00:57:02,756
Getting used to the job?

804
00:57:02,990 --> 00:57:05,492
No, I don't think I ever will.

805
00:57:06,927 --> 00:57:09,530
Actually, to tell you the truth...

806
00:57:09,963 --> 00:57:11,798
I was thinking of quitting.

807
00:57:13,667 --> 00:57:16,270
But I've quit quitting.

808
00:57:23,544 --> 00:57:24,945
I see.

809
00:57:25,646 --> 00:57:28,582
Do support her then.

810
00:57:28,615 --> 00:57:31,285
I wouldn't say I'm of much use yet.

811
00:57:31,318 --> 00:57:32,886
I'll aim for average first.

812
00:57:35,756 --> 00:57:37,591
Ms. Horai, I'll go get your coffee.

813
00:57:37,624 --> 00:57:39,560
You're still here?

814
00:57:40,527 --> 00:57:45,198
That story about Marie Antoinette?
I was so moved.

815
00:57:45,232 --> 00:57:48,702
Fashion is all about
creating dreams for people, huh?

816
00:57:49,069 --> 00:57:50,003
Dreams?

817
00:57:51,371 --> 00:57:52,606
You believed that crap?

818
00:57:53,206 --> 00:57:56,577
I've never heard of Marie Antoinette
ever gardening.

819
00:57:58,912 --> 00:58:00,147
You lied?

820
00:58:01,815 --> 00:58:02,649
50 million yen.

821
00:58:03,951 --> 00:58:08,255
We'll be the first magazine
that Togo Tomari is featured in.

822
00:58:08,288 --> 00:58:11,925
Once other designer brands see it,
they'll come rushing to us.

823
00:58:13,727 --> 00:58:18,799
How much do you think we'll make
from advertisements with that cover?

824
00:58:20,767 --> 00:58:21,835
50 million yen.

825
00:58:24,104 --> 00:58:27,441
I'd say that pays
for my little performance.

826
00:58:30,310 --> 00:58:31,411
Advertisements?

827
00:58:34,247 --> 00:58:37,884
If you buy a 50 million yen
advertisement from me,

828
00:58:37,918 --> 00:58:39,519
I'll bow down to you, too.

829
00:58:42,656 --> 00:58:45,359
Are you awake from your dream now?

830
00:58:50,430 --> 00:58:52,199
The devil's grin...

831
00:59:00,073 --> 00:59:02,943
Thank you for everything.

832
00:59:04,845 --> 00:59:06,279
You're like a hero.

833
00:59:07,014 --> 00:59:07,748
A hero?

834
00:59:08,415 --> 00:59:11,151
Showing up whenever I need help.

835
00:59:12,285 --> 00:59:15,188
Then can you do me a favor next?

836
00:59:16,223 --> 00:59:21,261
Sure! But it's not payday yet,
so it'll have to wait.

837
00:59:23,363 --> 00:59:24,564
Be my girlfriend.

838
00:59:30,470 --> 00:59:32,005
Come again?

839
00:59:32,906 --> 00:59:34,508
I want you to be my girlfriend.

840
00:59:40,847 --> 00:59:41,648
Girlfriend?

841
00:59:42,683 --> 00:59:44,284
Just pretend is fine.

842
00:59:44,317 --> 00:59:49,356
Wait, hold on. Girlfriend?
A pretend girlfriend?

843
00:59:50,891 --> 00:59:51,758
Pretend?

844
00:59:52,426 --> 00:59:54,795
- Pretend.
- Pretend...

845
00:59:55,028 --> 00:59:59,232
I told my mom I had a girlfriend
to get her to stop prying.

846
01:00:01,435 --> 01:00:03,403
I want a girlfriend like you.

847
01:00:04,738 --> 01:00:05,505
For pretend.

848
01:00:07,541 --> 01:00:09,142
For just one day.

849
01:00:12,913 --> 01:00:14,514
Okay, just one day then.

850
01:00:15,415 --> 01:00:16,650
Thank you!

851
01:00:16,950 --> 01:00:18,952
Is next weekend okay?

852
01:00:19,553 --> 01:00:22,989
I just need you to persuade my sister.
Mom will listen to her.

853
01:00:23,457 --> 01:00:24,458
Will you meet her?

854
01:00:28,328 --> 01:00:30,230
Um...

855
01:00:31,431 --> 01:00:32,799
Let me introduce you.

856
01:00:33,266 --> 01:00:34,434
My sister.

857
01:00:45,378 --> 01:00:45,746
What do you like about him?

858
01:00:45,746 --> 01:00:46,780
Next episode

859
01:00:46,780 --> 01:00:48,115
- The gap?
- The gap.

860
01:00:48,148 --> 01:00:49,483
It's our secret.

861
01:00:49,516 --> 01:00:51,518
I'll give you an average job.

862
01:00:51,551 --> 01:00:52,986
You may leave now.

863
01:00:53,019 --> 01:00:56,423
She's being mean to me
because I'm dating you.

864
01:00:56,456 --> 01:00:57,190
You say you want to be average
because you don't want to strive.

865
01:00:57,190 --> 01:01:00,193
This drama is fictional
